
Introduction to the N-body problem using NagBody codes
Mario A. Rodriguez-Meza

Useful material and papers of some of the numerical codes included in NagBody package.


References:

1. B.W. Kernighan and D.M. Ritchie, The C Programming Language. Second Edition. (Prentice Hall, Englewood Cliffs, 1988).

2. Kyle Loudon Mastering algorithms with C

3. W.H. Press, S.A. Teukolsky, W.T. Vetterling, and B.P. Flannery, Numerical Recipes, third edition. (Cambridge University Press, New York, 1992).

4. Forsythe G E, Malcolm M A, and Moler C B 1977 Computer Methods for Mathematical Computations. (Englewood Cliffs, N. J.: Prentice Hall).

5. D. Kahaner, C. Moler, and S. Nash, Numerical Methods and Software. (Prentice Hall, Engelwood Cliffs, 1989).

6. R.W. Hockney and J.W. Eastwood, Computer Simulation Using Particles. (McGraw-Hill, 1981).

7. S. Pfalzner and P. Gibbon, Many-Body Tree Methods in Physics. (Cambridge University Press, New York, 1996).

8.  M.P. Allen and D.J. Tildesley, {\em Computer Simulation of Liquids}. (Oxford University, New York, 1993).

9. D. C. Rapaport, The art of molecular dynamic simulation, 2nd edition. Cambridge University Press.

10. Mark Lutz, Learing python.

11. Wes McKinney, Python for data analysis.

12. Juan Nunez-Iglesias, Stéfan van der Walt and Harriet Dashnow, Elegant SciPy: The art of scientific python. 

13. Mario A. Rodríguez-Meza, El método del SPH y sus aplicaciones. Informe técnico CB-014/2002, ININ, 2002.


Easy readings:

1. Aristides S. Bouras and Loukia V. Ainarozidou, Python for tweens and Teens

2. Mario A. Rodríguez-Meza, Método de N-cuerpos en astrofísica.
https://www.researchgate.net/publication/316582859_Metodo_de_N-Cuerpos_en_Astrofisica

